Retook Seechi data again this month to better compare readings normally taken in the morning.  Took water sample for lab analysis.

Gordon Brushwyler (not Carol Brushwyler) took this data.  Jerry Kosterman is new trainee to help take early Spring data not taken before by Gordon + Carol (still in California).  No wildlife seen- loons must be gone.  No baby loons this year. Nest flooded over by high water.
Cloud cover 76%- Wind 4mph from ESE- Air temp 19?C (YSI Instrument)- Lake depth 52' (fishfinder)
